                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client who experiences allergic rhinitis asks the nurse about a nasal corticosteroid. How would the nurse reply?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIntranasal corticosteroids may be used to treat allergic rhinitis. The medication works locally and decreases inflammation. The client needs to be instructed to clear the nasal passages before use for best medication effectiveness. The client would take the medication regularly as prescribed in order for the effect to be achieved. The medication may take several days to achieve maximal effect because it works by decreasing inflammation.",
                        "id": "38097622cfca4df29e065030352fdf59",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
